devdoc.details: Implementation of a multi-token for Election.sol and ElectionFactory.sol. Every election contract has unique tokens.

params._election: address of election Requirements: -> only for owner -> `_election` does not exist

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

constructor.details: Constructor inherits from ERC1155 takes URI as identifier for Tokens

delElection(address).details: deletes an election struct already existing tokens of this election are not burned

params._election: address of election Requirements: -> only for owner -> `_election` exists

delegateVoteToken(address,address).details: delegates VoteToken to _receiver -> Emits a {TransferSingle} and {tokenEvent} event.

params._receiver: address of receiver Requirements: -> `_election` exists -> sender owns more than one Token

getVoteToken(address).details: mints VoteToken and send to msg.sender Emits a {TransferSingle} and {tokenEvent} event.

params._election: address of election Requirements: -> `_election` exists -> request of sender is new

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}. Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.
